01:04:22,486 --> 01:04:25,250
You-You imagined me?

884
01:04:25,322 --> 01:04:28,758
From the story,
<i>Buccaneer Ship?</i>

885
01:04:28,825 --> 01:04:31,419
"The Oceanographer
and the Blue Whale."

886
01:04:31,495 --> 01:04:33,486
But I'm not from a story.

887
01:04:41,838 --> 01:04:44,568
<i>[Edmund's Mother In Distance]</i>
<i>Edmund! Hurry up!</i>

888
01:04:44,641 --> 01:04:46,472
I'm from Brisbane.

889
01:04:46,543 --> 01:04:48,477
- Edmund!
- Edmund!

890
01:04:48,545 --> 01:04:51,946
<i>- Ladies and gentlemen, do not panic.</i>
- Edmund!

891
01:04:52,015 --> 01:04:54,745
Edmund!

892
01:04:54,818 --> 01:04:57,218
<i>[Mother]</i>
<i>Edmund! Hurry!</i>

893
01:04:57,287 --> 01:05:00,654
- It's time for you to leave now.
- Are you coming with us?

894
01:05:00,724 --> 01:05:04,319
- Why?
- It's not safe here.

895
01:05:04,394 --> 01:05:07,830
- But it's safe for me.
- But you're all alone.

896
01:05:09,699 --> 01:05:12,429
<i>[Mother]</i>
<i>Hurry up!</i>

897
01:05:12,502 --> 01:05:14,902
<i>Edmund!</i>

898
01:05:14,971 --> 01:05:17,235
Coming, Mother.

899
01:05:21,645 --> 01:05:24,808
<i>Edmund! Eddie?</i>

900
01:05:24,881 --> 01:05:27,782
Eddie, baby,
where have you been?

901
01:05:27,851 --> 01:05:30,183
We've been looking for you everywhere.
We've gotta get out of here.

902
01:05:30,253 --> 01:05:32,687
I met a girl!
Mum, I met a girl!

903
01:05:32,756 --> 01:05:36,021
Met a girl on this godforsaken island?
I'm happy for you.

904
01:05:36,093 --> 01:05:39,620
- A girl who lives here.
- Oh, you and your stories, Eddie!

905
01:05:39,696 --> 01:05:42,529
This island is no place for human beings.
I promise you that.

906
01:05:42,599 --> 01:05:44,760
Now, come on.
Wait for us! Please!

907
01:05:44,835 --> 01:05:47,599
<i>- [Edmund's Father] Wait for us!</i>
<i>- [Mother] We're coming!</i>

908
01:05:47,671 --> 01:05:49,696
<i>[Mother]</i>
<i>My God! Look at that!</i>

909
01:05:55,612 --> 01:05:59,013
Move it faster! Come on!

910
01:05:59,082 --> 01:06:02,984
How old are you now?
Eddie? Eddie?

911
01:06:03,053 --> 01:06:06,022
No more Game Boy, no more
television for a month.

912
01:06:06,089 --> 01:06:08,182
He's staying at home
forever.

913
01:06:11,528 --> 01:06:13,325
<i>[Thunder rumbling in the far distance]</i>

914
01:06:15,265 --> 01:06:19,292
Oh, no. Alex Rover, where are you?

915
01:06:19,369 --> 01:06:21,860
<i>[Thunderclaps]</i>

916
01:06:23,773 --> 01:06:26,970
[Gasping]
What's happening?

917
01:06:27,043 --> 01:06:29,136
Storm's changing course!
This is bad!

918
01:06:29,212 --> 01:06:31,578
- What?
- This is bad!

919
01:06:31,648 --> 01:06:34,879
Oh! Oh, this is it!
I'm gonna die!

920
01:06:34,951 --> 01:06:37,977
- I gotta agree with you on that one.
- What?

921
01:06:38,054 --> 01:06:41,319
Glass bubble hanging a hundred feet
above the middle of nowhere.

922
01:06:41,391 --> 01:06:45,225
Oh, I hate helicopters.
It's my Achilles' heel.

923
01:06:45,295 --> 01:06:47,763
You can't say that. You're a hero!

924
01:06:47,831 --> 01:06:51,494
I'm not a hero. I wish I were.
I'm just a helicopter pilot.

925
01:06:51,568 --> 01:06:56,096
- Oh!
- No, you're the hero, Alexandra.

926
01:06:56,173 --> 01:06:58,835
You came all the way down here
just to answer a distress call.

927
01:06:58,909 --> 01:07:03,369
You-You seized the moment,
claiming control of this part of your life!

928
01:07:03,446 --> 01:07:06,847
- [Gasps, gags] I'm gonna be sick.
<i>- No, no. No, no, no, no.</i>

929
01:07:06,917 --> 01:07:09,715
<i>- You can't. Oh!</i>
- What's that?

930
01:07:12,422 --> 01:07:14,617
I-I think
it's a cruise ship.

931
01:07:14,691 --> 01:07:18,252
<i>- I'm taking her down. We land there.</i>
- There?

932
01:07:18,328 --> 01:07:21,525
- [Shouting]
- No!

933
01:07:23,133 --> 01:07:24,896
[All screaming]

934
01:07:28,805 --> 01:07:31,035
South by southeast, full speed.

935
01:07:31,107 --> 01:07:33,268
Captain, you might
want to see this.

936
01:07:38,949 --> 01:07:41,247
Good Lord.

937
01:07:45,689 --> 01:07:49,056
[Gasping]
No more!

938
01:07:49,125 --> 01:07:52,060
No more! No more!

939
01:07:52,128 --> 01:07:55,393
Oh, thank you!
[Kisses]

940
01:07:55,465 --> 01:07:57,433
[Groaning]

941
01:07:57,500 --> 01:08:00,492
Who gave you permission
to land on my ship?

942
01:08:00,570 --> 01:08:03,471
- Who are you?
- I'm Alex Rover.

943
01:08:03,540 --> 01:08:05,838
Alex Rover? The adventurer?

944
01:08:05,909 --> 01:08:09,606
No! The writer!

945
01:08:09,679 --> 01:08:12,239
[Groans, spits]

946
01:08:12,315 --> 01:08:16,115
Come on now! Don't let me down here!
You're my last chance!

947
01:08:16,186 --> 01:08:18,450
Come on! Come on!

948
01:08:18,521 --> 01:08:20,614
That's it!

949
01:08:20,690 --> 01:08:22,715
Come on!

950
01:08:22,792 --> 01:08:26,250
[Laughing]
You did it!

951
01:08:26,329 --> 01:08:28,627
<i>Whoo-hoo! Okay. Come on!</i>

952
01:08:28,698 --> 01:08:33,192
Take me home!
Come on, Mother Nature!

953
01:08:33,270 --> 01:08:35,261
Take me back to Nim!

954
01:08:36,606 --> 01:08:38,938
Whoo-hoo!

955
01:08:39,009 --> 01:08:41,773
I know the coordinates perfectly well.
They're right in my head.

956
01:08:41,845 --> 01:08:44,905
It is, uh, 20 degrees south,
162 degrees west.

957
01:08:44,981 --> 01:08:46,972
There's a little girl there.

958
01:08:47,050 --> 01:08:49,314
There's no girl for 200 miles.

959
01:08:49,386 --> 01:08:51,718
<i>Oh, but she's-she's</i>
<i>all alone on an island.</i>

960
01:08:51,788 --> 01:08:54,222
And but-but what-

961
01:08:54,291 --> 01:08:56,486
Why is everybody looking at me
like I'm crazy?

962
01:08:56,559 --> 01:09:00,825
We've just come from the nearest island.
Trust me, no human being could survive there.

963
01:09:00,897 --> 01:09:03,889
- Just take me to the island!
- Young lady, we're battling

964
01:09:03,967 --> 01:09:07,164
Now, this ship is full throttle at sea and
we will not be coming about.

965
01:09:07,237 --> 01:09:09,205
Uh, but- I-
[Sighs]

966
01:09:09,272 --> 01:09:11,331
Captain, she's not
playing with a full deck.

967
01:09:11,408 --> 01:09:13,808
<i>You should have the medic come</i>
<i>and give her a little sedation.</i>

968
01:09:13,877 --> 01:09:15,811
<i>- Yeah, why don't you do that, huh?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

969
01:09:15,879 --> 01:09:17,972
- Eddie?
- He's probably after the dessert tray.

970
01:09:18,048 --> 01:09:21,711
I know she's there.
You know, I mean, I heard her voice.

971
01:09:21,785 --> 01:09:24,754
I didn't really hear her voice.
I got her e-mails.

972
01:09:24,821 --> 01:09:27,449
- You're not crazy.
- I'm not?

973
01:09:27,524 --> 01:09:30,516
I know it. I saw her.
She's real.

974
01:09:30,593 --> 01:09:33,858
- She-She's real?
- And she's on the island.

975
01:09:33,930 --> 01:09:36,524
Oh. Thanks. Thanks.

976
01:09:36,599 --> 01:09:40,365
The way you are handling it, the poise
with which you are handling this situation-

977
01:09:40,437 --> 01:09:43,429
- Ship's medic is on his way, Captain.
- Thank you, Ensign.

978
01:09:46,743 --> 01:09:49,678
- Hey! Hey! After her!
- Security!

979
01:09:55,652 --> 01:09:58,314
- [Gasps]
- Bingo in five minutes.

980
01:09:58,388 --> 01:10:00,322
Oh!

981
01:10:02,125 --> 01:10:04,923
Stop her!
Someone stop her!

982
01:10:07,664 --> 01:10:11,600
Oh, stupid suitcase!
Oh, you dropped soup.

983
01:10:11,668 --> 01:10:14,933
- I've got her!
<i>- Come on! Down here!</i>

984
01:10:15,004 --> 01:10:17,336
<i>[Captain]</i>
<i>Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!</i>

985
01:10:31,721 --> 01:10:33,712
<i>There she isl</i>

986
01:10:33,790 --> 01:10:37,385
<i>- Don't let her go!</i>
- [Screaming]

987
01:10:43,666 --> 01:10:46,294
<i>What on earth are you doing?</i>

988
01:10:46,369 --> 01:10:50,430
Just having
a nervous breakdown!

989
01:10:50,507 --> 01:10:52,839
<i>[Thunderclaps]</i>

990
01:11:13,096 --> 01:11:15,997
[Laughing]

991
01:11:16,065 --> 01:11:17,999
Whoo-hoo!

992
01:11:20,303 --> 01:11:22,794
[Gasping]

993
01:11:22,872 --> 01:11:26,035
[Shouts]

994
01:11:44,160 --> 01:11:46,856
No, no, no, no, no.
No, don't do this!

995
01:11:48,798 --> 01:11:51,528
[Shouts]

996
01:11:57,173 --> 01:12:01,405
I will not give up, Nim!
I will get back to you!

997
01:12:01,478 --> 01:12:03,469
I promise you!

998
01:12:09,986 --> 01:12:14,252
[Shouting]

999
01:12:16,426 --> 01:12:19,827
<i>[Shouts echoing]</i>

1000
01:12:22,966 --> 01:12:27,096
<i>[Shout Echoing Continues]</i>

1001
01:12:31,307 --> 01:12:33,241
Daddy?

1002
01:12:35,011 --> 01:12:36,945
Jack?

1003
01:12:37,981 --> 01:12:40,245
[Barks]

1004
01:12:53,429 --> 01:12:57,627
Daddy! Daddy!

1005
01:12:57,700 --> 01:12:59,725
Are you all right, Daddy?

1006
01:12:59,802 --> 01:13:01,599
Jack!

1007
01:13:01,671 --> 01:13:04,765
Selkie, Selkie, come on!
Jack needs us!

1008
01:13:04,841 --> 01:13:08,242
We have to save him!

1009
01:13:26,596 --> 01:13:30,054
Nim? Nim!

1010
01:13:42,211 --> 01:13:43,769
[Screams]

1011
01:14:16,779 --> 01:14:20,112
No!

1012
01:14:22,852 --> 01:14:25,616
[Inhales]

1013
01:15:02,492 --> 01:15:05,620
[Panting]
Nim.

1014
01:15:07,497 --> 01:15:09,897
Is that you? Nim?

1015
01:15:09,966 --> 01:15:13,231
Is that you? Nim.

1016
01:15:15,071 --> 01:15:17,539
Who are you?

1017
01:15:17,607 --> 01:15:20,599
Nim, I'm-
I'm Alex Rover.

1018
01:15:20,677 --> 01:15:23,669
Alex Rover?

1019
01:15:23,746 --> 01:15:26,237
Yeah, that's me.
[Chuckles]

1020
01:15:26,315 --> 01:15:30,217
But- No.
No, that's impossible.

1021
01:15:30,286 --> 01:15:34,723
Alex Rover, he's a man.
He's a hero.

1022
01:15:34,791 --> 01:15:37,851
He was gonna help me
find my dad.

1023
01:15:37,927 --> 01:15:40,725
He saves people.
He doesn't need saving.

1024
01:15:40,797 --> 01:15:43,425
I-I know.

1025
01:15:43,499 --> 01:15:46,866
<i>I'm-I'm Alexandra Rover.</i>

1026
01:15:48,104 --> 01:15:50,572
Alexandra?

1027
01:15:50,640 --> 01:15:53,336
I'm the writer
from San Francisco.

1028
01:15:53,409 --> 01:15:56,810
- The writer?
- Yeah. Well, you said you needed someone, so-

1029
01:15:56,879 --> 01:15:58,972
But I didn't say I needed you.

1030
01:15:59,048 --> 01:16:02,984
- You have to go.
- What are you talking about? I mean, I-

1031
01:16:03,052 --> 01:16:06,579
- You can't be here. You have to go
before my dad gets back.

1032
01:16:06,656 --> 01:16:09,591
This is our island, okay?
Our island alone.

1033
01:16:09,659 --> 01:16:12,822
And we don't want
anyone else here! Okay?

1034
01:16:12,895 --> 01:16:16,296
Please go. Go!

1035
01:16:25,341 --> 01:16:28,242
Follow her, Alexandra.

1036
01:16:28,311 --> 01:16:32,338
- You-You be quiet.
- No, I won't be quiet. She needs you.

1037
01:16:32,415 --> 01:16:35,782
What? She's- She's fine.
I mean, you heard her.

1038
01:16:35,852 --> 01:16:38,787
Apparently, she can do quite well.
She doesn't need me.

1039
01:16:38,855 --> 01:16:40,846
Of course she needs you.

1040
01:16:40,923 --> 01:16:43,289
And to be honest,
you kinda need her as well.

1041
01:16:43,359 --> 01:16:45,759
I mean,
where you gonna go?

1042
01:16:45,828 --> 01:16:49,423
But I- I'm gettin' outta here.
I'm gonna-

1043
01:16:49,499 --> 01:16:53,265
I'm gonna make a raft. I'm gonna,
like, make a little bonfire thing.

1044
01:16:53,336 --> 01:16:56,999
And-And then I'm gonna go home,
and I'm- I am never leaving.

1045
01:16:57,073 --> 01:16:59,837
You cannot be alone
for the rest of your life, Alexandra!

1046
01:16:59,909 --> 01:17:03,777
I'm not alone. I have you.

1047
01:17:05,281 --> 01:17:08,682
No, you don't.
No, you don't have me anymore.

1048
01:17:11,053 --> 01:17:14,216
I'm sorry, but I'm not gonna be
your crutch anymore.

1049
01:17:14,290 --> 01:17:18,192
[Sputters]
What?

1050
01:17:18,261 --> 01:17:21,355
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
Okay. Okay, look.

1051
01:17:21,430 --> 01:17:25,093
You-We just need to figure this thing out,
so you give me some ideas now. Come on.

1052
01:17:25,168 --> 01:17:28,626
- I'm sorry, love. It's over.
- What? What are you talking about?

1053
01:17:28,704 --> 01:17:31,070
Alexandra, I quit.

1054
01:17:32,775 --> 01:17:35,608
No more adventures.

1055
01:17:35,678 --> 01:17:38,306
- You're on your own.
- You-You-You can't quit.

1056
01:17:38,381 --> 01:17:43,546
I created you, and you have to do
what I say, not-not the opposite.

1057
01:17:43,619 --> 01:17:47,783
Good-bye, old friend.
Good luck.

1058
01:17:47,857 --> 01:17:51,918
But wa-Wait! Wait! Come back!

1059
01:17:51,994 --> 01:17:54,326
Go to the little girl!

1060
01:18:13,916 --> 01:18:15,850
[Sighs]

1061
01:18:16,085 --> 01:18:18,280
<i>[Animals calling]</i>

1062
01:18:18,354 --> 01:18:21,949
Nim? [Gasps]
Oh! What was that?

1063
01:18:22,024 --> 01:18:25,187
Oh, God. Just kill me now
and just get it over with.

1064
01:18:26,762 --> 01:18:28,696
[Spits]
Oh!

1065
01:18:28,764 --> 01:18:30,698
Eh! Aah.

1066
01:18:30,766 --> 01:18:33,701
Nim? Help!

1067
01:18:33,769 --> 01:18:37,967
<i>Uh, Nim? Help!</i>

1068
01:18:39,075 --> 01:18:41,066
[Growls]

1069
01:18:41,143 --> 01:18:45,102
<i>Can you hear me?</i>
<i>It's so dark out here!</i>

1070
01:18:45,181 --> 01:18:47,115
<i>Nim?</i>

1071
01:18:47,183 --> 01:18:50,983
Nim? Come on, help me.

1072
01:18:51,053 --> 01:18:54,819
I traveled halfway around the world.
I took a plane.

1073
01:18:54,891 --> 01:18:58,292
I took a helicopter. I- I stole a boat.

1074
01:18:58,361 --> 01:19:01,262
The least you can do is help me
get the last hundred yards.

1075
01:19:01,330 --> 01:19:04,163
- [Hisses]
- [Screaming]

1076
01:19:04,233 --> 01:19:06,497
Oh! Oh.

1077
01:19:06,569 --> 01:19:09,333
Nim? Nim.

1078
01:19:09,405 --> 01:19:11,566
I'm sorry
you don't want me here...

1079
01:19:11,641 --> 01:19:15,042
but I- I just thought
I was doin' the right thing.

1080
01:19:17,179 --> 01:19:20,012
<i>Oh. Oh, no.</i>

1081
01:19:20,082 --> 01:19:22,277
<i>Oh, no. Oh.</i>

1082
01:19:22,351 --> 01:19:24,410
- This is how it ends.
<i>- [Humming]</i>

1083
01:19:24,487 --> 01:19:27,285
A bright light in the darkness.

1084
01:19:27,356 --> 01:19:30,484
My- My worst nightmare-

1085
01:19:30,559 --> 01:19:33,357
Death by-
death by firefly!

1086
01:19:36,332 --> 01:19:39,267
[Whimpering]

1087
01:19:42,972 --> 01:19:45,998
[Sighs]
Thank you, Nim.

1088
01:19:48,277 --> 01:19:50,211
Oh!

1089
01:20:01,290 --> 01:20:03,622
<i>How long</i>
<i>have you lived here?</i>

1090
01:20:04,794 --> 01:20:06,819
As long as I can remember.

1091
01:20:06,896 --> 01:20:08,864
Wow.

1092
01:20:10,466 --> 01:20:12,457
You can go in if you want.

1093
01:20:30,553 --> 01:20:32,783
<i>"Jack Rusoe is a scientist</i>
<i>and a writer...</i>

1094
01:20:32,855 --> 01:20:36,814
<i>"living on a remote island</i>
<i>in the South Pacific.</i>

1095
01:20:36,892 --> 01:20:39,360
He won't tell anyone where it is."

1096
01:20:46,969 --> 01:20:49,028
Nim, how long has
your father been gone?

1097
01:20:51,640 --> 01:20:53,574
Four days.

1098
01:20:55,678 --> 01:20:59,671
But when Jack sets his mind
on something, it always gets done.

1099
01:20:59,749 --> 01:21:03,583
- He'll be back.
- I'm sure he will.

1100
01:21:04,787 --> 01:21:06,778
<i>You want any of this?</i>

1101
01:21:07,957 --> 01:21:10,653
What-What is it?

1102
01:21:10,726 --> 01:21:15,425
Well, these are mung beans
and gobo root.

1103
01:21:15,498 --> 01:21:18,524
And these are mealworms.

1104
01:21:19,902 --> 01:21:21,836
<i>Oh, uh-</i>
<i>[Chuckles]</i>

1105
01:21:21,904 --> 01:21:24,839
No, I'm-You know,
I-I'm just gonna-

1106
01:21:24,907 --> 01:21:26,898
I'm just gonna stick
with my soup.

1107
01:21:26,976 --> 01:21:28,910
Your soup?

1108
01:21:33,482 --> 01:21:36,246
<i>[Can Clatters]</i>

1109
01:21:36,318 --> 01:21:38,650
[Burps]

1110
01:21:38,721 --> 01:21:40,712
Sorry about that.

1111
01:21:43,392 --> 01:21:45,758
Here. Try some.

1112
01:21:50,266 --> 01:21:52,200
Uh, no.

1113
01:21:52,268 --> 01:21:54,828
[Inhales, exhales]

1114
01:21:54,904 --> 01:21:58,362
You didn't write
those Alex Rover books, did you?

1115
01:22:01,043 --> 01:22:03,807
- I didn't?
- No.

1116
